                                        520,
                                        2333,
                                        2027,
                                        2577
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": "Chow's theorem was used to prove some Wigner- type theorems for Hilbert Grassmannians formed by finite- dimensional subspaces 4 5 17. These Grassmannians are identified with the conjugacy classes of finite- rank projections. The adjacency relation can be interpreted as follows: the ranges of projections are adjacent if their difference is an operator of rank 2 (i.e. the smallest possible)."
                                }
                            ]
                        }
